item.description:
I am a Professor in the Department of Biostatistics and Medical Informatics and the Department of Population Health Sciences in the School of Medicine and Public Health at the University of Wisconsin-Madison. I have an affiliate appointment in the Department of Statistics.

I grew up in Duluth, Minnesota. I graduated from East High School in 1988. I earned a BA in Mathematics and Economics from the University of Minnesota-Duluth in 1992, an MS in Statistics from the University of Wisconsin-Madison in 1994, and a PhD in Statistics (Biostatistics option) from the University of Wisconsin-Madison in 1998.
